From: XR1710G-YYH-OC Builder <builder@xr1710g.local>
Date: 2026-07-13
Subject: [PATCH] kernel-defaults: run olddefconfig to resolve NEW kernel symbols

When CONFIG_ALL_KMODS=y is set, OpenWrt enables building every kmod
package, including drivers whose sub-options are NEW in the current
kernel version (e.g. IXGBE_IPSEC in Linux 6.18).  The kernel config
merge in Kernel/Configure/Default concatenates config fragments and
package overrides into .config.set, then copies it verbatim to .config
without running olddefconfig.  When the kernel build later invokes
syncconfig, it encounters (NEW) symbols that have no answer in .config
and aborts with:

  IPSec XFRM cryptography-offload acceleration (IXGBE_IPSEC) [Y/n/?] (NEW)
  make[8]: *** [scripts/kconfig/Makefile:85: syncconfig] Error 1
  ERROR: target/linux failed to build.

Fix: run $(KERNEL_MAKE) olddefconfig after .config is written so that
every NEW symbol is silently set to its default value.  Copy the
resolved .config back to .config.set so that .vermagic is computed on
the final, resolved configuration.  olddefconfig never changes existing
symbol values -- it only fills in defaults for symbols that are absent
-- so no functionality is lost.

This is a build-system fix, not a feature reduction: all selected
packages, kmods and patches remain exactly as before.
---
--- a/include/kernel-defaults.mk	2026-07-13 10:30:31.010173814 +0000
+++ b/include/kernel-defaults.mk	2026-07-13 10:30:31.042174012 +0000
@@ -125,6 +125,13 @@
 		cp $(LINUX_DIR)/.config.set $(LINUX_DIR)/.config; \
 		cp $(LINUX_DIR)/.config.set $(LINUX_DIR)/.config.prev; \
 	}
+	# Resolve NEW kernel config symbols (e.g. IXGBE_IPSEC) that appear
+	# when CONFIG_ALL_KMODS pulls in drivers whose sub-options are new
+	# in this kernel version.  Without olddefconfig, syncconfig aborts
+	# on (NEW) prompts in non-interactive mode.
+	$(KERNEL_MAKE) olddefconfig
+	cp $(LINUX_DIR)/.config $(LINUX_DIR)/.config.set
+	cp $(LINUX_DIR)/.config $(LINUX_DIR)/.config.prev
 	$(_SINGLE) [ -d $(LINUX_DIR)/user_headers ] || $(KERNEL_MAKE) $(if $(findstring uml,$(BOARD)),ARCH=$(ARCH)) INSTALL_HDR_PATH=$(LINUX_DIR)/user_headers headers_install
 	grep '=[ym]' $(LINUX_DIR)/.config.set | LC_ALL=C sort | $(MKHASH) md5 > $(LINUX_DIR)/.vermagic
 endef
